TP/3. HTTP/1.1 has persistent connections but requires additional headers, operates in a request-response mode, and ...\n\n8. 任务: 介绍HTTPS协议及其与HTTP的区别\n   状态: COMPLETED\n   摘要: The content explains the task of introducing HTTPS and its differences from HTTP. HTTPS is a secure data transfer protocol that adds encryption and integrity protection by incorporating SSL/TLS layers...\n\n9. 任务: 解释HTTP缓存机制\n   状态: COMPLETED\n   摘要: The content explains the HTTP caching mechanism, which is an optimization strategy between web browsers and servers to reduce data transfer and speed up page loading. Key components include caching co...\n\n"}],"max_tokens":8192,"temperature":0.7,"stream":false}
